  card: {
    question: '<h3>How much do you know about the HTML input <code>type="text"</code>?</h3>\n<p>What does the required attribute do in this code?</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;form>\n  &#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;label\n      for="name">First Name:\n    &#x3C;/label>\n    &#x3C;input\n      type="text" id="name"\n      name="name" required>\n  &#x3C;/div>\n  &#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;button>\n      Submit\n    &#x3C;/button>\n  &#x3C;/div>\n&#x3C;/form>\n</code></pre>\n<p>???</p>\n',
    answers: [
      {
        text: 'Makes the form not submittable without a value',
      },
      {
        text: 'Standard when creating any input type',
      },
      {
        text: 'makes the text turn blue',
      },
      {
        text: 'Makes the user type only text as input, no numbers allowed',
      },
    ],
    comment: '<p>The HTML input element of type <code>text</code> is used to create basic single line text fields.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;input type="text">\n</code></pre>\n<p>These text fields are useful for instance when you need single line inputs like for creating a new account.</p>\n<p>Example new account:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;form>\n  &#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;label\n      for="name">First Name:\n    &#x3C;/label>\n    &#x3C;input\n      type="text" id="name" name="fname"\n      placeholder="Enter First Name">\n  &#x3C;/div>\n  &#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;label\n      for="lname">Last Name:\n    &#x3C;/label>\n    &#x3C;input\n      type="text" id="lname" name="lname"\n      placeholder="Enter Last Name">\n  &#x3C;/div>\n  &#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;button>\n      Submit\n    &#x3C;/button>\n  &#x3C;/div>\n&#x3C;/form>\n</code></pre>\n<p><img src="%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%22136%22%3E%3Cg%20fill%3D%22none%22%20fill-rule%3D%22evenodd%22%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%22320%22%20height%3D%22136%22%20fill%3D%22%23FFF%22%20rx%3D%229%22%2F%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%23000%22%20font-family%3D%22ArialMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2216%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2220%22%20y%3D%2231%22%3EFirst%20Name%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%23000%22%20font-family%3D%22ArialMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2216%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2220%22%20y%3D%2271%22%3ELast%20Name%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3Cpath%20fill%3D%22%23FFF%22%20stroke%3D%22%23CCC%22%20d%3D%22M20.5%2075.5h130v18h-130zm0-40h130v18h-130z%22%2F%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%23000%22%20font-family%3D%22Arial-BoldMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2211.5%22%20font-weight%3D%22bold%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2227%22%20y%3D%22111%22%3ESubmit%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%2252%22%20height%3D%2217%22%20x%3D%2220.5%22%20y%3D%2298.5%22%20stroke%3D%22%23D3D3D3%22%20rx%3D%224%22%2F%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%237E757E%22%20font-family%3D%22ArialMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2213%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2224%22%20y%3D%2250%22%3EFirst%20Name%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3Ctext%20fill%3D%22%237E757E%22%20font-family%3D%22ArialMT%2C%20Arial%22%20font-size%3D%2213%22%3E%3Ctspan%20x%3D%2224%22%20y%3D%2290%22%3ELast%20Name%3C%2Ftspan%3E%3C%2Ftext%3E%3C%2Fg%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E" alt="form-single-inputs"></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If you have a single line input whose value should contain a date, URL, or an email, you should provide a more suitable input type than <code>type="text"</code>.</p>\n<p>Next, you can control the physical size of your input fields with the <code>size</code> attribute. The <code>size</code> attribute sets the width of the text field in terms of characters rather than pixels.</p>\n<p>Example: </p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;input type="text" size="10" >\n</code></pre>\n',
